Good Afternoon Raffaella,

I have requested payment is made to you today for the Temporary Accommodati=
on.

For the Vet Fees, these are not covered by your policy as your cat was not =
injured as a result of an accident with a motor vehicle as required by the =
policy.

Veterinary fees for your domestic pet
We=E2=80=99ll pay for veterinary fees if your domestic pet is injured in an=
 accident with a motor vehicle.
Any claim under this benefit will be excess-free.
We pay this benefit in addition to your contents sum insured.

Limit
We=E2=80=99ll pay up to $500 for each event

I have discussed the storage of contents items with our assessing team and =
have had confirmation that these currently able to be stored safely and sec=
urely in the property which we understand is also alarmed.  For this reason=
, we would not currently cover storage costs for you, as there is no need f=
or items to be stored in a commercial storage facility.  However, this is l=
ikely to change when the repairs actually start, at this time we can review=
 any change in circumstances and reimburse the reasonable costs for items t=
o be stored in a commercial storage facility.  Please note that any reimbur=
sement of costs will still need to go through our normal approval process.

Hopefully this covers off your questions, however I am more than happy to p=
rovide additional clarity if required.

Kind Regards



